docs.snippet: CINCINNATI, June 1 (AP)-- Tommy Helms's bases-loaded single climaxed a two-out, three-run rally in the ninth inning that lifted the Cincinnati Reds to a 7-6 victory over the Chicago Cubs tonight.

headline.main: REDS DOWN CUBS ON 3-RUN 9TH, 7-6; Helms's Single Caps Rally Coming After Two Outs

docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, June 3 (AP)--The United States defeated Argentina, 76-66, last night in the world basketball championships. The Soviet Union crushed Poland, 86-61, in the second game of the first double-header of the final round that ends June 11.

headline.main: U.S. Beats Argentine Five In World Tourney, 76-66
